BAUCHI – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Bauchi State has applauded the administration of Governor Bala Mohammed, saying it has an auspicious start and recorded tremendous achievements within his first 100 days in office. Alhaji Yayanuwa Zainabari, the state publicity secretary of the party who is also the chairman, Bauchi North chapter of the party, made the assertion on Monday during an interview with newsmen on the celebration of the 100 days of the governor in office coming up in the week. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “There is no gainsaying the fact that the governor has an auspicious start as immediately when he took over the mantle of leadership of the state, he wasted no time in justifying the confidence reposed in him by the electorate. “Within the first 100 days, he has flagged off road construction projects at areas that lack access roads and renovation of the dilapidated ones in both the state capital and other senatorial zones. “The first ones he flagged off in the state capital were construction and rehabilitation of four roads worth about N5 billion which included Ibrahim Bako to Maiduguri Road Bye-Pass, Sabon Kaura to Jos Road while those of Muda Lawal Market and Yakubun Bauchi Quarters would be rehabilitated” he said.